*gaim-0.59.8-r1 (13 Jan 2003)

  13 Jan 2003; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org> gaim-0.59.8-r1.ebuild,
  files/digest-gaim-0.59.8-r1 :
  Added ssl support via the encrypt plugin provided at
  gaim-encryption.sourcforge.net.  Also removed the gtk2 logic as
  all the gtk2 code has been ripped out as of this version.  Use
  gaim-cvs for a gtk2 enabled build of gaim.

*gaim-0.5.8 (08 Jan 2003)

  08 Jan 2003; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> :
  Version bump, just bug fixes, still awaiting 0.60 ;)  

*gaim-0.5.7 (29 Dec 2002)

  29 Dec 2002; Daniel Robbins <drobbins@gentoo.org>: updated to latest version
  of gaim, reworked deps to make them simpler, cleaned up the build code, and
  allowed gtk+ and glib version 2.2.x to satisfy their respective deps (closing
  bug 12641.) Unmasked for the 1.4 release for x86, ~ for ppc.

  23 Dec 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> :
  Fix glib and gtk+ deps, as it seems to work with versions 2.2.0 ...

*gaim-0.95.6 (11 Nov 2002)

